<subSubSection lastPageId="7" lastPageNumber="8" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="5.[264,1323,1703,1889]" lastBlockId="6.[264,1322,284,430]" lastPageId="6" lastPageNumber="7" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">
Head. Cephalic tubercles armed with three pairs of spines fused basally; first pair 
<number box="[1283,1294,1823,1849]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" value="1.0">1</number>
/ 
<number box="[1305,1320,1823,1849]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" value="5.0">5</number>
times longer than second, and placed above them; third pair ½ length of first pair and placed laterally (
<figureCitation box="[463,654,284,310]" captionStart="FIGURES 14 – 19" captionStartId="6.[264,382,1800,1824]" captionTargetBox="[338,1267,473,1774]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[245,1296,472,1796]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 14 – 19. Anthrax hylaios pupae: 14. General lateral view; 15. Cephalic tubercle, dorsal view; 16. Cephalic tubercle, lateral view; 17. Head, ventral view; 18. Anal tubercle, dorsal view; 19. Anal tubercle, lateral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/158278/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">
Figs. 
<number box="[531,560,284,310]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" value="15.0">15</number>
and 
<number box="[621,654,284,310]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" value="16.0">16</number>
</figureCitation>
). Central pair of spines with two pairs of setae, the first one on dorsal surface, near its base, second placed laterally on basal half of spine (
<figureCitation box="[1222,1309,324,350]" captionStart="FIGURES 14 – 19" captionStartId="6.[264,382,1800,1824]" captionTargetBox="[338,1267,473,1774]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[245,1296,472,1796]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 14 – 19. Anthrax hylaios pupae: 14. General lateral view; 15. Cephalic tubercle, dorsal view; 16. Cephalic tubercle, lateral view; 17. Head, ventral view; 18. Anal tubercle, dorsal view; 19. Anal tubercle, lateral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/158278/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">
Fig. 
<number box="[1276,1309,324,350]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" value="16.0">16</number>
</figureCitation>
). In ventral view, both anterior and posterior facial tubercles present, the first with a pair of setae placed laterally, additional pair on posterior margin (
<figureCitation box="[946,1033,404,430]" captionStart="FIGURES 14 – 19" captionStartId="6.[264,382,1800,1824]" captionTargetBox="[338,1267,473,1774]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[245,1296,472,1796]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 14 – 19. Anthrax hylaios pupae: 14. General lateral view; 15. Cephalic tubercle, dorsal view; 16. Cephalic tubercle, lateral view; 17. Head, ventral view; 18. Anal tubercle, dorsal view; 19. Anal tubercle, lateral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/158278/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">
Fig. 
<number box="[1001,1033,404,430]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" value="17.0">17</number>
</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<caption httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/158278/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" targetBox="[338,1267,473,1774]" targetPageId="6">
<paragraph blockId="6.[264,1323,1800,1901]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[264,457,1800,1824]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">FIGURES 14–19</emphasis>
. 
<taxonomicName box="[473,644,1801,1824]" class="Insecta" family="Bombyliidae" genus="Anthrax" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hylaios">
<emphasis box="[473,644,1801,1824]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">Anthrax hylaios</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
pupae: 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[732,758,1800,1824]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">14</emphasis>
. General lateral view; 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1011,1037,1800,1824]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">15</emphasis>
. Cephalic tubercle, dorsal view; 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[332,358,1837,1861]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">16</emphasis>
. Cephalic tubercle, lateral view; 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[722,749,1837,1861]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">17</emphasis>
. Head, ventral view; 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[986,1012,1837,1861]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">18</emphasis>
. Anal tubercle, dorsal view; 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[264,290,1877,1901]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">19</emphasis>
. Anal tubercle, lateral view.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph blockId="7.[264,1325,284,1230]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">
Thorax. With four pairs of setae, two pairs on dorsal surface placed close together, two pairs on lateral surface; prothoracic spiracle heavily sclerotized, dark brown, raised above surface and located immediately behind head (
<figureCitation box="[810,898,364,390]" captionStart="FIGURES 14 – 19" captionStartId="6.[264,382,1800,1824]" captionTargetBox="[338,1267,473,1774]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[245,1296,472,1796]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 14 – 19. Anthrax hylaios pupae: 14. General lateral view; 15. Cephalic tubercle, dorsal view; 16. Cephalic tubercle, lateral view; 17. Head, ventral view; 18. Anal tubercle, dorsal view; 19. Anal tubercle, lateral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/158278/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">
Fig. 
<number box="[865,898,364,390]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" value="14.0">14</number>
</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="7.[264,1325,284,1230]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">
Abdomen. Segment I with transverse row of long setae, interrupted in center; segment II–V with transverse rows of chitinous rods intercalated with long, thin setae, row of setae interrupted in center; segments VI–VII with reduced chitinous rods, resembling small spines, intercalated with thin setae; segment VIII with row of reduced chitinous rods; pleura with tufts of strong and long setae, sternites with transverse rows of strong setae, interrupted in center; the row on segment VII is complete; anal tubercle with three pairs of spines, central pair completely fused, except at apex, with two pairs of projections, first pair located on the middle of the spine and second pair placed ventrally, near the base of each spine; second and third pairs of spines tiny and placed on the base of first pair, on dorsal and ventral surfaces respectively. Additional single spine on dorsal base of the tubercle (
<figureCitation box="[375,563,804,830]" captionStart="FIGURES 14 – 19" captionStartId="6.[264,382,1800,1824]" captionTargetBox="[338,1267,473,1774]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[245,1296,472,1796]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 14 – 19. Anthrax hylaios pupae: 14. General lateral view; 15. Cephalic tubercle, dorsal view; 16. Cephalic tubercle, lateral view; 17. Head, ventral view; 18. Anal tubercle, dorsal view; 19. Anal tubercle, lateral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/158278/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">
Figs. 
<number box="[443,472,804,830]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" value="18.0">18</number>
and 
<number box="[531,563,804,830]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" value="19.0">19</number>
</figureCitation>
). Abdominal spiracles slightly darker and more sclerotized than surrounding area, raised above surface and placed laterally on segments I–VII.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="7.[264,1325,284,1230]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">
Female: Sternite VIII without row of setae. (Length: 
<quantity box="[947,1057,884,910]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.6199999999999999" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" unit="mm" value="16.2">16.2 mm</quantity>
. Head width: 
<quantity box="[1224,1320,884,910]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.1" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" unit="mm" value="2.1">2.1 mm</quantity>
. Thorax width: 
<quantity box="[438,531,924,950]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.1" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" unit="mm" value="3.1">3.1 mm</quantity>
. Abdominal width: 
<quantity box="[765,855,924,950]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.5" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" unit="mm" value="3.5">3.5 mm</quantity>
tapering to 
<quantity box="[996,1086,924,950]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.6" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" unit="mm" value="1.6">1.6 mm</quantity>
on anal segment) Hosts: 
<taxonomicName box="[353,513,964,990]" class="Insecta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="order">Hymenoptera</taxonomicName>
­ 
<taxonomicName box="[551,683,964,989]" class="Insecta" family="Crabronidae" genus="Trypoxylon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[551,683,964,989]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">Trypoxylon</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
sp.; 
<taxonomicName authority="Moure, 1999" authorityName="Moure" authorityYear="1999" box="[753,1178,964,990]" class="Insecta" family="Apidae" genus="Tetrapedia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="garofaloi">
